'The FT6236U touch controller uses I2C address 0x38, although this is not explicitly stated in the datasheet.', 0, 10),

('q3-2', 'lesson-3-quiz', 'Why should touch detection use interrupts instead of polling?', 'multiple_choice',
'["Interrupts are required by the FT6236U","Polling uses less power","Interrupts provide faster response and save power","Polling is more accurate"]',
'Interrupts provide faster response and save power',
'Interrupt-driven touch detection allows the system to sleep until a touch occurs, saving power while still providing immediate response to user input.', 1, 10),

('q3-3', 'lesson-3-quiz', 'What does the BMA423 accelerometer have built-in?', 'multiple_choice',
'["GPS receiver","Step counting algorithm","Temperature sensor","Bluetooth radio"]',
'Step counting algorithm',
'The BMA423 includes a built-in step counting algorithm that processes accelerometer data internally, providing a cumulative step count.', 2, 10),

('q3-4', 'lesson-3-quiz', 'How should coordinates be extracted from the FT6236U registers?', 'multiple_choice',
